name: The Fellowship of the Bling
description:
Everyone knows that Hobbits are drawn to shiny things like seagulls to a landfill. Well, Bilbo wasn't the only one who got something precious. Help the fellowship show off some of the goodies they pilfered on their travels through Middle Earth.

Printed with gold foil ink on green American Apparel tees.

name: Grey vs Gray
description:
Many historians fail to mention that the REAL cause of the Revolutionary War was not the "taxation without representation" issue, but rather the fight between the British and Americans over how to spell this color. OK, so I totally made that up, but it is an entertaining topic to puzzle over nonetheless.

Printed on a Black American Apparel tee.

name: Karaoke Rockstar
description:
Way before American Idol pimped out aspiring musicians for the masses, karaoke allowed people an outlet for their supposed musical genius. And what else is as entertaining when it's both great and horrendous? Show confidence in your karaoke skills with this tee.

Printed on a charcoal American Apparel tee.

name: Storytime With Lincoln
description:
I think behind the patriotic rhetoric about the union, behind the stoic and patient exterior, part of Lincoln just wanted to say, "Screw these annoying rebellious redneck punks and their plantation-owning backers, why don't they just go home and leave me alone." Maybe the only one he could share these feelings with was his son Tad at storytime.

Printed on Silver Grey American Apparel tees.

name: Mogadishu Marauders
description:
Do you want to show your friends that youâ€™re up to date on current events? Interested in pretending that you knew the capital of Somalia was Mogadishu? Excited to commemorate the epic battle between Islamic Fundamentalist pirates and the very essence of Western capitalism: international shipping? If you answered yes to any of the above questions, Mogadishu Marauders is the shirt for you.

Printed on a 90% cotton heather grey and black ringer tee.
